Actor.name: Actor
Actor.doc:
Actor types are {@link Object} types that are capable of performing
activities.
Actor.label: Actor

ActorTypeName.name: ActorTypeName
ActorTypeName.doc: A string representation of an actor type name.
ActorTypeName.label: ActorTypeName

AuthenticatedDocumentLoaderFactory.name: AuthenticatedDocumentLoaderFactory
AuthenticatedDocumentLoaderFactory.doc:
A factory function that creates an authenticated {@link DocumentLoader} for
a given identity.  This is used for fetching documents that require
authentication.
AuthenticatedDocumentLoaderFactory.label: AuthenticatedDocumentLoaderFactory

DocumentLoader.name: DocumentLoader
DocumentLoader.doc: A JSON-LD document loader that fetches documents from the Web.
DocumentLoader.label: DocumentLoader

InboundService.name: InboundService
InboundService.doc:
The third party sites this server can retrieve messages from for combined
display with regular traffic.
InboundService.label: InboundService

JsonValue.name: JsonValue
JsonValue.doc: The type of the result of parsing JSON.
JsonValue.label: JsonValue

OutboundService.name: OutboundService
OutboundService.doc:
The third party sites this server can publish messages to on the behalf
of a user.
OutboundService.label: OutboundService

PUBLIC_COLLECTION.name: PUBLIC_COLLECTION
PUBLIC_COLLECTION.doc:
The special public collection for [public addressing].  *Do not mutate this
object.*

[public addressing]: https://www.w3.org/TR/activitypub/#public-addressing
PUBLIC_COLLECTION.label: PUBLIC_COLLECTION

Protocol.name: Protocol
Protocol.doc: The protocols supported on this server.
Protocol.label: Protocol

exportMultibaseKey().name: exportMultibaseKey
exportMultibaseKey().doc:
Exports a public key in [Multibase] format.

[Multibase]: https://www.w3.org/TR/vc-data-integrity/#multibase-0
exportMultibaseKey().label: exportMultibaseKey()

exportSpki().name: exportSpki
exportSpki().doc: Exports a public key in PEM-SPKI format.
exportSpki().label: exportSpki()

fetchDocumentLoader().name: fetchDocumentLoader
fetchDocumentLoader().doc:
A JSON-LD document loader that utilizes the browser's `fetch` API.

This loader preloads the below frequently used contexts:

- <https://www.w3.org/ns/activitystreams>
- <https://w3id.org/security/v1>
- <https://w3id.org/security/data-integrity/v1>
- <https://www.w3.org/ns/did/v1>
- <https://w3id.org/security/multikey/v1>
fetchDocumentLoader().label: fetchDocumentLoader()

getActorClassByTypeName().name: getActorClassByTypeName
getActorClassByTypeName().doc: Gets the actor class by the given type name.
getActorClassByTypeName().label: getActorClassByTypeName()

getActorHandle().name: getActorHandle
getActorHandle().doc:
Gets the actor handle, of the form `@username@domain`, from the given actor
or an actor URI.
getActorHandle().label: getActorHandle()

getActorTypeName().name: getActorTypeName
getActorTypeName().doc: Gets the type name of the given actor.
getActorTypeName().label: getActorTypeName()

getAuthenticatedDocumentLoader().name: getAuthenticatedDocumentLoader
getAuthenticatedDocumentLoader().doc:
Gets an authenticated {@link DocumentLoader} for the given identity.
Note that an authenticated document loader intentionally does not cache
the fetched documents.
getAuthenticatedDocumentLoader().label: getAuthenticatedDocumentLoader()

importSpki().name: importSpki
importSpki().doc: Imports a PEM-SPKI formatted public key.
importSpki().label: importSpki()

isActor().name: isActor
isActor().doc: Checks if the given object is an {@link Actor}.
isActor().label: isActor()

kvCache().name: kvCache
kvCache().doc: Decorates a {@link DocumentLoader} with a cache backed by a {@link Deno.Kv}.
kvCache().label: kvCache()

lookupObject().name: lookupObject
lookupObject().doc:
Looks up an ActivityStreams object by its URI (including `acct:` URIs)
or a fediverse handle (e.g., `@user@server` or `user@server`).
lookupObject().label: lookupObject()

nodeInfoToJson().name: nodeInfoToJson
nodeInfoToJson().doc: Converts a {@link NodeInfo} object to a JSON value.
nodeInfoToJson().label: nodeInfoToJson()

signRequest().name: signRequest
signRequest().doc: Signs a request using the given private key.
signRequest().label: signRequest()

verifyRequest().name: verifyRequest
verifyRequest().doc:
Verifies the signature of a request.

Note that this function consumes the request body, so it should not be used
if the request body is already consumed.  Consuming the request body after
calling this function is okay, since this function clones the request
under the hood.
verifyRequest().label: verifyRequest()

ActorDispatcher.name: ActorDispatcher
ActorDispatcher.doc: A callback that dispatches an {@link Actor} object.
ActorDispatcher.label: ActorDispatcher

ActorKeyPairDispatcher.name: ActorKeyPairDispatcher
ActorKeyPairDispatcher.doc: A callback that dispatches a key pair for an actor.
ActorKeyPairDispatcher.label: ActorKeyPairDispatcher

ActorKeyPairsDispatcher.name: ActorKeyPairsDispatcher
ActorKeyPairsDispatcher.doc: A callback that dispatches key pairs for an actor.
ActorKeyPairsDispatcher.label: ActorKeyPairsDispatcher

AuthorizePredicate.name: AuthorizePredicate
AuthorizePredicate.doc: A callback that determines if a request is authorized or not.
AuthorizePredicate.label: AuthorizePredicate

CollectionCounter.name: CollectionCounter
CollectionCounter.doc: A callback that counts the number of items in a collection.
CollectionCounter.label: CollectionCounter

CollectionCursor.name: CollectionCursor
CollectionCursor.doc: A callback that returns a cursor for a collection.
CollectionCursor.label: CollectionCursor

CollectionDispatcher.name: CollectionDispatcher
CollectionDispatcher.doc: A callback that dispatches a collection.
CollectionDispatcher.label: CollectionDispatcher

InboxErrorHandler.name: InboxErrorHandler
InboxErrorHandler.doc: A callback that handles errors in an inbox.
InboxErrorHandler.label: InboxErrorHandler

InboxListener.name: InboxListener
InboxListener.doc: A callback that listens for activities in an inbox.
InboxListener.label: InboxListener

KvKey.name: KvKey
KvKey.doc: A key for a key-value store.  An array of one or more strings.
KvKey.label: KvKey

NodeInfoDispatcher.name: NodeInfoDispatcher
NodeInfoDispatcher.doc: A callback that dispatches a {@link NodeInfo} object.
NodeInfoDispatcher.label: NodeInfoDispatcher

ObjectAuthorizePredicate.name: ObjectAuthorizePredicate
ObjectAuthorizePredicate.doc: A callback that determines if a request is authorized or not.
ObjectAuthorizePredicate.label: ObjectAuthorizePredicate

ObjectDispatcher.name: ObjectDispatcher
ObjectDispatcher.doc: A callback that dispatches an object.
ObjectDispatcher.label: ObjectDispatcher

OutboxErrorHandler.name: OutboxErrorHandler
OutboxErrorHandler.doc: A callback that handles errors during outbox processing.
OutboxErrorHandler.label: OutboxErrorHandler

ParseUriResult.name: ParseUriResult
ParseUriResult.doc: A result of parsing an URI.
ParseUriResult.label: ParseUriResult

SharedInboxKeyDispatcher.name: SharedInboxKeyDispatcher
SharedInboxKeyDispatcher.doc:
A callback that dispatches the key pair for the authenticated document loader
of the {@link Context} passed to the shared inbox listener.
SharedInboxKeyDispatcher.label: SharedInboxKeyDispatcher

respondWithObject().name: respondWithObject
respondWithObject().doc: Responds with the given object in JSON-LD format.
respondWithObject().label: respondWithObject()

respondWithObjectIfAcceptable().name: respondWithObjectIfAcceptable
respondWithObjectIfAcceptable().doc:
Responds with the given object in JSON-LD format if the request accepts
JSON-LD.
respondWithObjectIfAcceptable().label: respondWithObjectIfAcceptable()

doesActorOwnKey().name: doesActorOwnKey
doesActorOwnKey().doc: Checks if the actor of the given activity owns the specified key.
doesActorOwnKey().label: doesActorOwnKey()

exportJwk().name: exportJwk
exportJwk().doc: Exports a key in JWK format.
exportJwk().label: exportJwk()

generateCryptoKeyPair().name: generateCryptoKeyPair
generateCryptoKeyPair().doc: Generates a key pair which is appropriate for Fedify.
generateCryptoKeyPair().label: generateCryptoKeyPair()

getKeyOwner().name: getKeyOwner
getKeyOwner().doc:
Gets the actor that owns the specified key.  Returns `null` if the key has no
known owner.
getKeyOwner().label: getKeyOwner()

importJwk().name: importJwk
importJwk().doc: Imports a key from JWK format.
importJwk().label: importJwk()

sign().name: sign
sign().doc: Signs a request using the given private key.
sign().label: sign()

verify().name: verify
verify().doc:
Verifies the signature of a request.

Note that this function consumes the request body, so it should not be used
if the request body is already consumed.  Consuming the request body after
calling this function is okay, since this function clones the request
under the hood.
verify().label: verify()

integrateFetchOptions().name: integrateFetchOptions
integrateFetchOptions().doc: Create options for the `federation` object to integrate with Fresh.
integrateFetchOptions().label: integrateFetchOptions()

integrateHandler().name: integrateHandler
integrateHandler().doc:
Create a Fresh middleware handler to integrate with the {@link Federation}
object.
integrateHandler().label: integrateHandler()

ContextDataFactory.name: ContextDataFactory
ContextDataFactory.doc:
A factory function to create a context data for the {@link Federation}
object.
ContextDataFactory.label: ContextDataFactory

federation().name: federation
federation().doc: Create a Hono middleware to integrate with the {@link Federation} object.
federation().label: federation()

Accept.name: Accept
Accept.doc:
Indicates that the `actor` accepts the `object`.  The `target` property can be
used in certain circumstances to indicate the context into which the `object`
has been accepted.
Accept.label: Accept

Activity.name: Activity
Activity.doc:
An Activity is a subtype of {@link Object} that describes some form of action
that may happen, is currently happening, or has already happened.
The {@link Activity} type itself serves as an abstract base type for all types
of activities.  It is important to note that the {@link Activity} type itself
does not carry any specific semantics about the kind of action being taken.
Activity.label: Activity

Add.name: Add
Add.doc:
Indicates that the `actor` has added the `object` to the `target`.
If the `target` property is not explicitly specified, the target would need
to be determined implicitly by context.  The `origin` can be used to identify
the context from which the `object` originated.
Add.label: Add

Announce.name: Announce
Announce.doc:
Indicates that the `actor` is calling the `target`'s attention the `object`.

The `origin` typically has no defined meaning.
Announce.label: Announce

Arrive.name: Arrive
Arrive.doc:
An `IntransitiveActivity` that indicates that the `actor` has arrived at the `location`.
The `origin` can be used to identify the context from which the `actor` originated.
The `target` typically has no defined meaning.
Arrive.label: Arrive

Article.name: Article
Article.doc: Represents any kind of multi-paragraph written work.
Article.label: Article

Audio.name: Audio
Audio.doc: Represents an audio document of any kind.
Audio.label: Audio

Block.name: Block
Block.doc:
Indicates that the `actor` is blocking the `object`.  Blocking is a stronger
form of {@link Ignore}.  The typical use is to support social systems that
allow one user to block activities or content of other users.  The `target`
and `origin` typically have no defined meaning.
Block.label: Block

Collection.name: Collection
Collection.doc:
A `Collection` is a subtype of {@link Object} that represents ordered or
unordered sets of {@link Object} or {@link Link} instances.

Refer to the Activity Streams 2.0 Core specification for a complete
description of the Collection type.
Collection.label: Collection

CollectionPage.name: CollectionPage
CollectionPage.doc:
Used to represent distinct subsets of items from a `Collection`.
Refer to the Activity Streams 2.0 Core for a complete description of
the `CollectionPage` object.
CollectionPage.label: CollectionPage

Create.name: Create
Create.doc: Indicates that the `actor` has created the `object`.
Create.label: Create

CryptographicKey.name: CryptographicKey
CryptographicKey.doc: A key owned by an actor.
CryptographicKey.label: CryptographicKey

DataIntegrityProof.name: DataIntegrityProof
DataIntegrityProof.doc:
A proof that can be added to any activity or object, allowing recipients to
verify the identity of the actor and the integrity of the data.
DataIntegrityProof.label: DataIntegrityProof

Delete.name: Delete
Delete.doc:
Indicates that the `actor` has deleted the `object`.  If specified,
the `origin` indicates the context from which the `object` was deleted.
Delete.label: Delete

Document.name: Document
Document.doc: Represents a document of any kind.
Document.label: Document

FetchError.name: FetchError
FetchError.doc: Error thrown when fetching a JSON-LD document failed.
FetchError.label: FetchError

Flag.name: Flag
Flag.doc:
Indicates that the `actor` is "flagging" the `object`.  Flagging is defined
in the sense common to many social platforms as reporting content as being
inappropriate for any number of reasons.
Flag.label: Flag

Follow.name: Follow
Follow.doc:
Indicates that the `actor` is "following" the `object`.  Following is defined
in the sense typically used within Social systems in which the actor is
interested in any activity performed by or on the object.  The `target` and
`origin` typically have no defined meaning.
Follow.label: Follow

Group.name: Group
Group.doc: Represents a formal or informal collective of Actors.
Group.label: Group

Hashtag.name: Hashtag
Hashtag.doc:
A specialized {@link Link} that represents an #hashtag.

See also <https://swicg.github.io/miscellany/#Hashtag>.
Hashtag.label: Hashtag

Ignore.name: Ignore
Ignore.doc:
Indicates that the `actor` is ignoring the `object`.  The `target` and
`origin` typically have no defined meaning.
Ignore.label: Ignore

Image.name: Image
Image.doc: An image document of any kind.
Image.label: Image

IntransitiveActivity.name: IntransitiveActivity
IntransitiveActivity.label: IntransitiveActivity

Invite.name: Invite
Invite.doc:
A specialization of `Offer` in which the `actor` is extending an invitation
for the `object` to the `target`.
Invite.label: Invite

Join.name: Join
Join.doc:
Indicates that the `actor` has joined the `object`.
The `target` and `origin` typically have no defined meaning.
Join.label: Join

LanguageString.name: LanguageString
LanguageString.doc: A language-tagged string which corresponds to the `rdf:langString` type.
LanguageString.label: LanguageString

Leave.name: Leave
Leave.doc:
Indicates that the `actor` has left the `object`.
The `target` and `origin` typically have no meaning.
Leave.label: Leave

Like.name: Like
Like.doc:
Indicates that the `actor` likes, recommends or endorses the `object`.
The `target` and `origin` typically have no defined meaning.
Like.label: Like

Link.name: Link
Link.doc:
A Link is an indirect, qualified reference to a resource identified by a URL.
The fundamental model for links is established by RFC 5988. Many of the
properties defined by the Activity Vocabulary allow values that are either
instances of {@link Object} or {@link Link}. When a {@link Link} is used,
it establishes a qualified relation connecting the subject (the containing
object) to the resource identified by the `href`. Properties of
the {@link Link} are properties of the reference as opposed to properties of
the resource.
Link.label: Link

Listen.name: Listen
Listen.doc: Indicates that the `actor` has listened to the `object`.
Listen.label: Listen

Mention.name: Mention
Mention.doc: A specialized {@link Link} that represents an @mention.
Mention.label: Mention

Multikey.name: Multikey
Multikey.doc:
Represents a key owned by an actor according to [FEP-521a: Representing
actor's public keys.][1]

[1]: https://codeberg.org/fediverse/fep/src/branch/main/fep/521a/fep-521a.md
Multikey.label: Multikey

NodeInfo.name: NodeInfo
NodeInfo.doc: A NodeInfo object as defined in the NodeInfo 2.1 schema.
NodeInfo.label: NodeInfo

Note.name: Note
Note.doc:
Represents a short written work typically less than a single paragraph in
length.
Note.label: Note

Object.name: Object
Object.doc:
Describes an object of any kind. The Object type serves as the base type for
most of the other kinds of objects defined in the Activity Vocabulary,
including other Core types such as {@link Activity},
{@link IntransitiveActivity}, {@link Collection} and
{@link OrderedCollection}.
Object.label: Object

Offer.name: Offer
Offer.doc:
Indicates that the actor is offering the object.
If specified, the target indicates the entity to which
the object is being offered.
Offer.label: Offer

OrderedCollection.name: OrderedCollection
OrderedCollection.doc:
A subtype of {@link Collection} in which members of the logical collection
are assumed to always be strictly ordered.
OrderedCollection.label: OrderedCollection

OrderedCollectionPage.name: OrderedCollectionPage
OrderedCollectionPage.doc:
Used to represent ordered subsets of items from an `OrderedCollection`.
Refer to the Activity Streams 2.0 Core for a complete description of
the `OrderedCollectionPage` object.
OrderedCollectionPage.label: OrderedCollectionPage

Place.name: Place
Place.doc:
Represents a logical or physical location.  See [5.3 Representing
Places](https://www.w3.org/TR/activitystreams-vocabulary/#places)
for additional information.
Place.label: Place

Profile.name: Profile
Profile.doc:
A {@link Profile} is a content object that describes another {@link Object},
typically used to describe [Actor
Type](https://www.w3.org/TR/activitystreams-vocabulary/#actor-types) objects.
The {@link Profile.describes} property is used to reference the object being
described by the profile.
Profile.label: Profile

PropertyValue.name: PropertyValue
PropertyValue.doc: A pair of property name and value.
PropertyValue.label: PropertyValue

Question.name: Question
Question.doc:
Represents a question being asked.  Question objects are an extension of
{@link IntransitiveActivity}.  That is, the Question object is an Activity,
but the direct object is the question itself and therefore it would not
contain an `object` property.

Either of the `anyOf` and `oneOf` properties *may* be used to express possible
answers, but a Question object *must not* have both properties.
Question.label: Question

Recipient.name: Recipient
Recipient.doc:
The object that can be a recipient of an activity.

Note that every {@link Actor} is also a {@link Recipient}.
Recipient.label: Recipient

Reject.name: Reject
Reject.doc:
Indicates that the `actor` is rejecting the `object`.  The `target` and
`origin` typically have no defined meaning.
Reject.label: Reject

Relationship.name: Relationship
Relationship.doc:
Describes a relationship between two individuals.
The {@link Relationship.subject} and {@link Relationship.object} properties
are used to identify the connected individuals.

See [5.2 Representing Relationships Between
Entities](https://www.w3.org/TR/activitystreams-vocabulary/#connections)
for additional information.
Relationship.label: Relationship

RemoteDocument.name: RemoteDocument
RemoteDocument.doc:
A remote JSON-LD document and its context fetched by
a {@link DocumentLoader}.
RemoteDocument.label: RemoteDocument

Remove.name: Remove
Remove.doc:
Indicates that the `actor` is removing the `object`.  If specified,
the `origin` indicates the context from which the `object` is being removed.
Remove.label: Remove

ResourceDescriptor.name: ResourceDescriptor
ResourceDescriptor.doc:
Describes a resource.  See also
[RFC 7033 section 4.4](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7033#section-4.4).
ResourceDescriptor.label: ResourceDescriptor

Service.name: Service
Service.doc: Represents a service of any kind.
Service.label: Service

Services.name: Services
Services.doc: The third party sites this server can connect to via their application API.
Services.label: Services

Software.name: Software
Software.doc: Metadata about server software in use.
Software.label: Software

Tombstone.name: Tombstone
Tombstone.doc:
A `Tombstone` represents a content object that has been deleted.
It can be used in {@link Collection}s to signify that there used to be
an object at this position, but it has been deleted.
Tombstone.label: Tombstone

Undo.name: Undo
Undo.doc:
Indicates that the `actor` is undoing the `object`.  In most cases,
the `object` will be an {@link Activity} describing some previously performed
action (for instance, a person may have previously "liked" an article but,
for whatever reason, might choose to undo that like at some later point in
time).

The `target` and `origin` typically have no defined meaning.
Undo.label: Undo

Update.name: Update
Update.doc:
Indicates that the `actor` has updated the `object`.  Note, however,
that this vocabulary does not define a mechanism for describing the actual
set of modifications made to `object`.

The `target` and `origin` typically have no defined meaning.
Update.label: Update

Video.name: Video
Video.doc: Represents a video document of any kind.
Video.label: Video

ActorCallbackSetters.name: ActorCallbackSetters
ActorCallbackSetters.label: ActorCallbackSetters

ActorKeyPair.name: ActorKeyPair
ActorKeyPair.doc: A pair of a public key and a private key in various formats.
ActorKeyPair.label: ActorKeyPair

CollectionCallbackSetters.name: CollectionCallbackSetters
CollectionCallbackSetters.doc: Additional settings for a collection dispatcher.
CollectionCallbackSetters.label: CollectionCallbackSetters

Federation.name: Federation
Federation.doc:
An object that registers federation-related business logic and dispatches
requests to the appropriate handlers.

It also provides a middleware interface for handling requests before your
web framework's router; see {@link Federation.handle}.
Federation.label: Federation

FederationKvPrefixes.name: FederationKvPrefixes
FederationKvPrefixes.doc: Prefixes for namespacing keys in the Deno KV store.
FederationKvPrefixes.label: FederationKvPrefixes

FederationParameters.name: FederationParameters
FederationParameters.doc: Parameters for initializing a {@link Federation} instance.
FederationParameters.label: FederationParameters

InProcessMessageQueue.name: InProcessMessageQueue
InProcessMessageQueue.doc:
A message queue that processes messages in the same process.
Do not use this in production as it does not persist messages.
InProcessMessageQueue.label: InProcessMessageQueue

InboxListenerSetters.name: InboxListenerSetters
InboxListenerSetters.doc: Registry for inbox listeners for different activity types.
InboxListenerSetters.label: InboxListenerSetters

KvStore.name: KvStore
KvStore.doc: An abstract interface for a key-value store.
KvStore.label: KvStore

KvStoreSetOptions.name: KvStoreSetOptions
KvStoreSetOptions.doc: Additional options for setting a value in a key-value store.
KvStoreSetOptions.label: KvStoreSetOptions

MemoryKvStore.name: MemoryKvStore
MemoryKvStore.doc:
A key-value store that stores values in memory.
Do not use this in production as it does not persist values.
MemoryKvStore.label: MemoryKvStore

MessageQueue.name: MessageQueue
MessageQueue.doc: An abstract interface for a message queue.
MessageQueue.label: MessageQueue

MessageQueueEnqueueOptions.name: MessageQueueEnqueueOptions
MessageQueueEnqueueOptions.doc: Additional options for enqueuing a message in a queue.
MessageQueueEnqueueOptions.label: MessageQueueEnqueueOptions

ObjectCallbackSetters.name: ObjectCallbackSetters
ObjectCallbackSetters.doc: Additional settings for an object dispatcher.
ObjectCallbackSetters.label: ObjectCallbackSetters

RespondWithObjectOptions.name: RespondWithObjectOptions
RespondWithObjectOptions.doc:
Options for the {@link respondWithObject} and
{@link respondWithObjectIfAcceptable} functions.
RespondWithObjectOptions.label: RespondWithObjectOptions

Router.name: Router
Router.doc:
URL router and constructor based on URI Template
([RFC 6570](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6570)).
Router.label: Router

RouterError.name: RouterError
RouterError.doc: An error thrown by the {@link Router}.
RouterError.label: RouterError

SendActivityOptions.name: SendActivityOptions
SendActivityOptions.doc:
Options for {@link Context.sendActivity} method and
{@link Federation.sendActivity} method.
SendActivityOptions.label: SendActivityOptions

SenderKeyPair.name: SenderKeyPair
SenderKeyPair.doc: A key pair for an actor who sends an activity.
SenderKeyPair.label: SenderKeyPair

DenoKvMessageQueue.name: DenoKvMessageQueue
DenoKvMessageQueue.doc: Represents a message queue adapter that uses Deno KV store.
DenoKvMessageQueue.label: DenoKvMessageQueue

DenoKvStore.name: DenoKvStore
DenoKvStore.doc: Represents a key-value store implementation using Deno's KV store.
DenoKvStore.label: DenoKvStore
